                    "description": "Key Words: Astronomical instrumentation, Space Instrumentation, Optical system designing, Alignment & Performance evaluation, Clean room laboratory, Solar coronagraph, Polarimeter.\n\nPrevious project: Ultra Violet Imaging Telescope (UVIT)\nNature of work:\n\n     1. Aligned and evaluated the optical performance of UVIT, a payload on ASTROSAT-I satellite. It contains two Ritchey Chretien telescopes of 380mm aperture. Precision theodolites are used for preliminary alignment and fine alignment and performance evaluation is done by measuring the system wavefront error using Zygo interferometer. One of these twin telescopes operate in Near UV, Visible and the other one in Far UV wavelength range. \n\n      2. Carried out through focus PSF measurements for the two telescopes in vacuum environment against a calibrated collimator. And detectors are positioned at best focus of the telescope.\n\n     3. Calibrated various UV filters and UV Gratings used in UVIT for transmission profiles, focus shifts and transmission efficiencies respectively. \n\n     4. Measured the quantum efficiency of  UV detectors against a NIST calibrated photodiode.\n\nCurrent project: Visible Emission Line Solar-coronagraph (VELC).\nNature of work:\n\n     1. Designed the optics of VELC, a payload on ADITYA-I. VELC is aimed at studying solar corona from space. It contains one imaging and  3 spectroscopy channels. Carried out detailed tolerance analysis, thermal analysis and ghost image analysis etc. Generated fabrication and alignment tolerances. \n\n     2. Designed experiments to test various components in the VELC like, narrow band filters, diffraction gratings, dichroic beam splitters.\n\n     3. Designed alignment and performance evaluation schemes of VELC payload .\n\n     4. Working on the realization of the component level and payload level test and calibration setups.",
